                    <h5 id="options" class="mt-4">Options</h5>
                    <p>The client object supports an <code class="inline-code">$options</code> array to pass in general configuration details and data for the request.
                        Supported keys in the options array are:</p>
                    <ul class="list-disc ml-8">
                        <li class="mb-1"><code class="inline-code">base_uri</code><span class="text-sm"> - the base URI for re-submitting many requests with the same client to different endpoints on the same domain</span></li>
                        <li class="mb-1"><code class="inline-code">method</code><span class="text-sm"> - the request method (GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE, etc.)</span></li>
                        <li class="mb-1"><code class="inline-code">headers</code><span class="text-sm"> - an array of request headers</span></li>
                        <li class="mb-1"><code class="inline-code">user_agent</code><span class="text-sm"> - the user agent string</span></li>
                        <li class="mb-1"><code class="inline-code">query</code><span class="text-sm"> - an array of request query data - reserved for only a URL-encoded query string</span></li>
                        <li class="mb-1"><code class="inline-code">data</code><span class="text-sm"> - an array of request data - can be any request data</span></li>
                        <li class="mb-1"><code class="inline-code">files</code><span class="text-sm"> - an array of files on disk to be sent with the request</span></li>
                        <li class="mb-1"><code class="inline-code">type</code><span class="text-sm"> - set the request type (URL-form, JSON, XML or multipart/form)</span></li>
                        <li class="mb-1"><code class="inline-code">Request::URLENCODED</code><span class="text-sm"> - <code class="inline-code">application/x-www-form-urlencoded</code></span></li>
                        <li class="mb-1"><code class="inline-code">Request::JSON</code><span class="text-sm"> - <code class="inline-code">application/json</code></span></li>
                        <li class="mb-1"><code class="inline-code">Request::XML</code><span class="text-sm"> - <code class="inline-code">application/xml</code></span></li>
                        <li class="mb-1"><code class="inline-code">Request::MULTIPART</code><span class="text-sm"> - <code class="inline-code">multipart/form-data</code></span></li>
                        <li class="mb-1"><code class="inline-code">auto</code><span class="text-sm"> - trigger automatic content negotiation and return the parsed content, if possible (boolean)</span></li>
                        <li class="mb-1"><code class="inline-code">async</code><span class="text-sm"> - trigger an asynchronous request (boolean)</span></li>
                        <li class="mb-1"><code class="inline-code">verify_peer</code><span class="text-sm"> - enforce or disallow verifying the host for SSL connections (boolean)</span></li>
                        <li class="mb-1"><code class="inline-code">allow_self_signed</code><span class="text-sm"> - allow or disallow the use of self-signed certificates for SSL connections (boolean)</span></li>
                        <li class="mb-1"><code class="inline-code">force_custom_method</code><span class="text-sm"> - for Curl only. Forces the use of <code class="inline-code">CURLOPT_CUSTOMREQUEST</code> (boolean)</span></li>
                    </ul>
